text.paragraph:
Prolonged experience with levetiracetam tablets in pregnant women has not identified a drug-associated risk of major birth defects or miscarriage, based on published literature, which includes data from pregnancy registries and reflects experience over two decades [see 
                                 Error! Hyperlink reference not valid.
                                 ]. In animal studies, levetiracetam produced developmental toxicity (increased embryofetal and offspring mortality, increased incidences of fetal structural abnormalities, decreased embryofetal and offspring growth, neurobehavioral alterations in offspring) at doses similar to human therapeutic doses [see 
                                 Error! Hyperlink reference not valid.
                                 ].
